{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a9cc48f9-088b-4bb2-b9fb-14d43e51ef0f","content":"Use MAUI's conditional compilation with `#if` directives in `MauiProgram.cs`:\n\n```csharp\npublic static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()\n{\n    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();\n    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();\n\n#if ANDROID\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Android.AndroidNotificationService>();\n#elif IOS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.iOS.IosNotificationService>();\n#elif WINDOWS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Windows.WindowsNotificationService>();\n#endif\n\n    return builder.Build();\n}\n```\n\nEach implementation lives under its respective `Platforms/` folder (e.g., `Platforms/Android/AndroidNotificationService.cs`), which are already conditionally compiled per-platform by the SDK. This ensures only the relevant implementation is compiled and registered on each target, so it won't break on any platform.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9d593638-1883-4305-8680-003a4fb09a34","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI dependency injection — specifically how to register platform-specific implementations of an `INotificationService` in `MauiProgram.cs`. This is a general knowledge question, not a codebase task.","outputTokens":318,"requestId":"DC06:19AB05:F1DF1:12BBAF:69F54CD0"},"id":"a5884d22-000b-4715-9b41-f7d67340d146","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:01:10.670Z","parentId":"58af99ab-3479-4e64-9f39-ab62df023305"}
